Name: Common substances for allergy and intolerance documentation including refutations
AllergyIntoleranceCategory
Title: AllergyIntoleranceCategory
Description: Category of an identified substance associated with allergies or intolerances.

Name: AllergyIntoleranceCriticality
Title: AllergyIntoleranceCriticality
Description: Estimate of the potential clinical harm, or seriousness, of a reaction to an identified substance.

Name: AllergyIntoleranceType
Title: AllergyIntoleranceType
Description: Identification of the underlying physiological mechanism for a Reaction Risk.

Name: AllergyIntoleranceClinicalStatusCodes
Title: AllergyIntolerance Clinical Status Codes
Description: Preferred value set for AllergyIntolerance Clinical Status.

Name: AllergyIntoleranceVerificationStatusCodes
Title: AllergyIntolerance Verification Status Codes
Description: Preferred value set for AllergyIntolerance Verification Status.

Name: CarePlanActivityKind
Title: Care Plan Activity Kind
Description: Resource types defined as part of FHIR that can be represented as in-line definitions of a care plan activity.

Name: CarePlanActivityOutcome
Title: Care Plan Activity Outcome
Description: Example codes indicating the outcome of a care plan activity. Note that these are in no way complete and might not even be appropriate for some uses.

Name: CarePlanActivityStatus
Title: CarePlanActivityStatus
Description: Codes that reflect the current state of a care plan activity within its overall life cycle.

Name: CarePlanCategory
Title: Care Plan Category
Description: Example codes indicating the category a care plan falls within.  Note that these are in no way complete and might not even be appropriate for some uses.

Name: CarePlanIntent
Title: Care Plan Intent
Description: Codes indicating the degree of authority/intentionality associated with a care plan.

Name: CareTeamCategory
Title: Care Team category
Description: Indicates the type of care team.

Name: CareTeamStatus
Title: CareTeamStatus
Description: Indicates the status of the care team.

Name: SNOMEDCTClinicalFindings
Title: SNOMED CT Clinical Findings
Description: This value set includes all the "Clinical finding" [SNOMED CT](http://snomed.info/sct) codes - concepts where concept is-a 404684003 (Clinical finding (finding)).

Name: CommonLanguages
Title: Common Languages
Description: This value set includes common codes from BCP-47 (http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47)

Name: SNOMEDCTMedicationCodes
Title: SNOMED CT Medication Codes
Description: This value set includes all drug or medicament substance codes and all pharmaceutical/biologic products from SNOMED CT - provided as an exemplar value set.

Name: ProcedureCodes(SNOMEDCT)
Title: Procedure Codes (SNOMED CT)
Description: Procedure Code: All SNOMED CT procedure codes.

Name: AllergyIntoleranceSeverity
Title: AllergyIntoleranceSeverity
Description: Clinical assessment of the severity of a reaction event as a whole, potentially considering multiple different manifestations.

Name: RequestStatus
Title: RequestStatus
Description: Codes identifying the lifecycle stage of a request.

Name: SNOMEDCTRouteCodes
Title: SNOMED CT Route Codes
Description: This value set includes all Route codes from SNOMED CT - provided as an exemplar.

Name: SubstanceCode
Title: Substance Code
Description: This value set contains concept codes for specific substances. It includes codes from [SNOMED](http://snomed.info/sct) where concept is-a 105590001 (Substance (substance)) and where concept is-a 373873005 (Pharmaceutical / biologic product (product))

Name: NarrativeStatus
Title: US Core Narrative Status
Description: The US Core Narrative Status Value Set limits the text status for the resource narrative.
